This product is a service layer built on top of the following open-source
projects, which remain the property of their respective authors:

  - RAG-Anything — https://github.com/HKUDS/RAG-Anything (MIT License)
      Multimodal document parsing and the RAGAnything ingestion pipeline.

  - LightRAG — https://github.com/HKUDS/LightRAG (MIT License)
      Knowledge-graph construction, dual-level retrieval, and the Postgres
      (pgvector + Apache AGE) storage backends.

  - MinerU — https://github.com/opendatalab/MinerU (MinerU Open Source
      License, a custom license based on Apache-2.0)
      Document layout parsing / OCR, pulled in transitively via RAG-Anything
      (raganything[all] -> mineru[core]) and used to parse uploaded documents.

      ATTRIBUTION REQUIRED. The MinerU Open Source License requires that any
      online service provided to third parties "based on MinerU" clearly and
      prominently indicate, in the service interface or public documentation,
      that MinerU is used. This NOTICE and the PolyGraphRAG README both state
      that document parsing is powered by MinerU. Failure to attribute
      terminates the license automatically. A separate commercial license is
      required only above 100M monthly active users or USD 20M monthly revenue
      (not applicable here). PolyGraphRAG pins mineru>=3.1.0 to stay on this
      Apache-based license; earlier MinerU releases were AGPL-3.0.

A full inventory of bundled third-party components and their licenses —
required when redistributing the built Docker image — is in
THIRD_PARTY_LICENSES.md.

PolyGraphRAG adds a production FastAPI service around these libraries:
multi-workspace isolation, asynchronous ingest-job tracking, per-role model
provider routing, file management, and interactive graph visualization.

The Apache AGE edge-property fix that older deployments carried as a vendored
patch was contributed upstream by Oleksandr Kushnir
(https://github.com/oleksandr-kushnir) and merged into LightRAG as
HKUDS/LightRAG#3052; PolyGraphRAG now relies on it via the pinned lightrag-hku
version in requirements.txt rather than shipping a patch.
